[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering what happens if the native runtime doesn’t have metadata for new test classes — especially regarding the TCK agent. In CI, tests run natively post-generation, but does the metadata come from the agent? I need to clarify that. 
[thinking] 
[thinking] Existing metadata needs to be intact, as test classes should be app code reachable. Since reflection requires metadata, any failures could stem from missing constructors in new classes. I also wonder whether there's a dedicated test file per class, and it seems we shouldn't edit metadata directly. I should probably check for a git diff before finalizing decisions!
