[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering method checks**\n\nI need to think about whether to check for empty methods in Checkstyle. Usually, an empty block doesn’t have a comment, and the current style might allow for that. The public top-level tests seem fine. \n\nNow, I'm also wondering about dynamic class names, specifically in the ProgrammaticClientEndpoint inner class. It includes a `$`, which could be okay depending on file naming rules. However, the overloaded connectToServer methods might present a potential issue with URI schemes and null configurators that could arise before getting to the metadata phase. This needs further reasoning!\n\n**Evaluating test class metadata**\n\nI’m considering what happens if the native runtime doesn’t have metadata for new test classes — especially regarding the TCK agent. In CI, tests run natively post-generation, but does the metadata come from the agent? I need to clarify that. \n\nExisting metadata needs to be intact, as test classes should be app code reachable. Since reflection requires metadata, any failures could stem from missing constructors in new classes. I also wonder whether there's a dedicated test file per class, and it seems we shouldn't edit metadata directly. I should probably check for a git diff before finalizing decisions!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_002ab245fc2530ac016a2477a516b48193a1dfa6357059db90\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJHexutDn0a4e0uT6FI9vG5JiVX-JldC63Z7lHj_ou77ARuZ7AiB3F69w06HaIBJs8jfRxEKFDb4XHqnafaRl-33dEVARpvjHzfHocofUz6M89_YFhqI87IuTXc7TP8Rp_w0GkXhmbAjd0yv6zkNDn4nBi7V9jQSOZJEbiB6bsqOCGEPGYxY7eJOx_lwr-Zav12BKwiDLauYYQvFAsrkTC8w_yAhofNVZ9LHO5s9ynnwr7yzQVpnez6yLisOfJM5aQ8qtEEGbq3wS6dgNcJqzhJJ-vLnJ3xX712ZGhlmelBmCMAZvpk9ty6mfG7pDjYi19rQ2Ba8yDrDlCM2Cktrt40Rd_sGUHgnl8QPRoWYIM4UasXE687ZrZCZx7u750tjwYgS0k4CA1VS3glvHlYe-mKSWQ8ngHbDauUOkGaoZX-M7tYrLK9xPxvcqIwP9GRuRFpw7A